part of the WooCommerce.

00:08:15.960 --> 00:08:19.260
Accessibility starts
with a well-structured HTML

00:08:20.190 --> 00:08:25.100
and the WooCommerce platform
has a built-in support for semantic HTML.

00:08:25.500 --> 00:08:29.970
Using semantic HTML
tags like header, footer, main,

00:08:30.240 --> 00:08:34.180
so this creates a well-structured website
that is easier for the assistive

00:08:34.280 --> 00:08:37.280
technology users like screen reader
or speech

00:08:37.710 --> 00:08:41.280
recognition users
to interpret the content.

00:08:43.220 --> 00:08:45.550
Of course, we all know that

00:08:45.650 --> 00:08:50.860
native HTML provides accessibility without
requiring additional external resources,

00:08:51.330 --> 00:08:55.700
so WooCommerce also allows
the user to integrate ARIA as well.

00:08:56.960 --> 00:09:00.670
When it comes to the interactive elements
like product galleries,

00:09:01.100 --> 00:09:04.110
carousels, filters, and shopping carts.

00:09:04.710 --> 00:09:07.340
When we are using these features provided

00:09:07.340 --> 00:09:10.310
with a dynamic shopping experience,

00:09:10.410 --> 00:09:14.250
there can be sometimes a bit difficulty
for the users with disability

00:09:14.350 --> 00:09:19.220
to navigate through such content,
this is where the ARIA comes into play.

00:09:19.920 --> 00:09:23.620
ARIA attribute helps to make the complex

00:09:23.720 --> 00:09:26.860
interactive components understandable
for the assistive technology.

00:09:27.400 --> 00:09:30.500
For example,
if there is an expandable control,

00:09:30.870 --> 00:09:36.140
so providing ARIA expanded attribute
will help the user, especially the screen

00:09:36.240 --> 00:09:40.810
reader user, to understand the expanded
and collapsed state of the control.

00:09:41.510 --> 00:09:45.350
HTML, along with the right use of ARIA,
obviously provide

00:09:45.450 --> 00:09:50.790
assistive technology compatibility
and also a proper keyboard navigation.

00:09:51.390 --> 00:09:53.920
Another key feature regarding

00:09:54.020 --> 00:09:57.020
WooCommerce is that customizable element.

00:09:57.260 --> 00:10:00.260
For a long vision user,
especially when they are

00:10:00.390 --> 00:10:03.160
accessing an e-commerce site,

00:10:03.260 --> 00:10:06.530
if they want to adjust the font size
or contrast

00:10:07.270 --> 00:10:11.950
setting or even the text spacing,
if they want to use it comfortably.

00:10:13.770 --> 00:10:18.150
Then WooCommerce really shines over here
because it allows the user

00:10:18.410 --> 00:10:24.090
to provide a toolbar where
they can select these options.

00:10:24.890 --> 00:10:27.320
That's the functionality of WooCommerce

00:10:27.320 --> 00:10:29.420
that we are getting additional.

00:10:33.330 --> 00:10:36.330
These are the features that WooCommerce
is obviously providing us,

00:10:36.800 --> 00:10:40.370
because of the accessibility features
and all the WooCommerce stands out

00:10:40.680 --> 00:10:42.620
when it comes to plugins.

00:10:42.840 --> 00:10:48.180
Even though the majority
of the accessibility

00:10:48.280 --> 00:10:55.280
lies with developers and other testers
who are there in the industries,

00:10:55.650 --> 00:10:58.890
still there is a chance
that we can improve these plugins

00:10:59.250 --> 00:11:01.490
when it comes to accessibility.

00:11:01.590 --> 00:11:04.590
While WooCommerce templates
provide a starting point

00:11:04.690 --> 00:11:09.700
for the accessibility navigation,
not all interactive elements are optimized

00:11:09.800 --> 00:11:13.100
for users who rely solely on keyboard.

00:11:14.170 --> 00:11:19.240
For example, as I have already mentioned,
like product filters and pop-ups and all.

00:11:21.640 --> 00:11:23.970
Sometimes what happens,

00:11:24.450 --> 00:11:30.710
they suffer from poor tabbing orders,
missing focus indicators,

00:11:31.150 --> 00:11:38.430
and such limitations will create confusion
for the users who is using the site.

00:11:38.760 --> 00:11:43.330
Here WooCommerce can make sure
that interactive elements can be accessed

00:11:43.430 --> 00:11:48.440
and navigated using the keyboard alone
and keyboard focus indicator

00:11:48.540 --> 00:11:51.540
should be visible and consistent
throughout the site.

00:11:53.540 --> 00:11:57.180
As I have already mentioned regarding
the templates of the WooCommerce,

00:11:57.750 --> 00:12:00.750
we have one more thing that is forms.

00:12:00.920 --> 00:12:04.690
Obviously for a e-commerce website,
forms are really important.

00:12:05.090 --> 00:12:07.930
To complete the purchase order
or the shipping order,

00:12:08.170 --> 00:12:09.890
a form is really important.

00:12:09.990 --> 00:12:13.960
Yes, WooCommerce do provide such forms,
but the only concern here

00:12:14.060 --> 00:12:17.800
is that the error messages
and the feedbacks are not conveyed

00:12:17.900 --> 00:12:19.670
for the screen reader user.

00:12:19.770 --> 00:12:22.500
To resolve this,
we can improve the accessibility

00:12:22.500 --> 00:12:25.510
of the form validation
by adding an ARIA-like feature

00:12:25.810 --> 00:12:28.410
to the dynamic success
and the error messages,

00:12:28.510 --> 00:12:31.850
or we can provide a clear and concise
error message

00:12:32.080 --> 00:12:35.580
that can be programmatically
tied to the form first.

00:12:36.380 --> 00:12:38.820
This will ensure that the users
are informed of

00:12:38.910 --> 00:12:42.220
the issues and can be guided
to resolve and complete

00:12:42.330 --> 00:12:44.590
the checkout or the payment process

00:12:44.710 --> 00:12:46.400
or any other forms.

00:12:48.800 --> 00:12:51.230
Next is regarding the skipping.

00:12:51.330 --> 00:12:54.640
We all know that
when there is a multiple--

00:12:55.670 --> 00:12:59.570
Especially for the keyboard-only user,
when navigating through a web page.

00:13:00.170 --> 00:13:02.580
In the header section,
if there are multiple links

00:13:02.680 --> 00:13:07.080
and we have to go through
multiple web pages.

00:13:08.150 --> 00:13:12.550
It's a bit frustrating experience
for the keyboard-only user to tap

00:13:12.650 --> 00:13:16.990
through the same content again and again
just to reach to the main content.

00:13:18.090 --> 00:13:20.590
Most of the website,
if you see there is a pattern

00:13:20.590 --> 00:13:23.600
that the header and the footer are fixed.

00:13:24.830 --> 00:13:26.800
When navigating through these control

00:13:26.800 --> 00:13:30.840
in multiple pages,
this might create frustration

00:13:30.940 --> 00:13:35.680
for the user,
so it is always good to have a skip link.

00:13:35.780 --> 00:13:40.650
WooCommerce default
themes does not have this currently,

00:13:40.750 --> 00:13:43.950
so implementing
that would be a better option.

00:13:46.120 --> 00:13:51.960
Coming to the plugins, custom
plugins are something

00:13:52.060 --> 00:13:55.860
that we use in our day-to-day
life when we are building

00:13:56.060 --> 00:14:01.940
a website, not just e-commerce website,
even other website also.

00:14:02.040 --> 00:14:05.810
A third-party plugins, mostly
I can see that an iframe is used

00:14:06.070 --> 00:14:08.940
or any other chatbot is used, or something

00:14:09.020 --> 00:14:11.510
like a third-party tool is always used.

00:14:12.450 --> 00:14:16.450
We have to make sure that these plugins
are 100% accessible

00:14:16.550 --> 00:14:22.120
so that it wouldn't limit
the user to access the content.

00:14:24.440 --> 00:14:25.430
For example,

00:14:25.430 --> 00:14:29.300
like third-party plugins
that adds interactive features

00:14:29.400 --> 00:14:32.900
such as product galleries,
sliders or pop-ups

00:14:33.000 --> 00:14:37.140
which may have proper keyboard
accessibility or ARIA support.

00:14:37.810 --> 00:14:42.810
There we can keep a strict guidelines
for the plugins

00:14:43.080 --> 00:14:45.220
that we can use in our website.

00:14:49.080 --> 00:14:51.790
When it comes to product pages,

00:14:51.890 --> 00:14:55.190
WooCommerce provides
a wide variety of themes

00:14:55.290 --> 00:14:59.430
where you can select
multiple products images.

00:14:59.530 --> 00:15:03.000
Your can upload that to your website
so the user can have

00:15:03.100 --> 00:15:06.530
a full-on experience
to see all the products on the page.

00:15:07.710 --> 00:15:10.750
When these images
are added to the screens,

00:15:11.370 --> 00:15:15.610
so there is a requirement
of alternate text for these images.

00:15:15.980 --> 00:15:18.150
That part will be covered later.

00:15:18.250 --> 00:15:21.920
But as of now,
the WooCommerce doesn't enforce it

00:15:22.120 --> 00:15:26.590
that the images that we are uploading
should have an alternate text.

00:15:26.690 --> 00:15:28.770
