00:19:34.370 --> 00:19:39.140
Now let's see how we can design the website
by keeping inclusivity in mind.

00:19:40.210 --> 00:19:43.210
Let's start with a basic one,
that is the color contrast.

00:19:43.940 --> 00:19:48.820
When you're browsing through the website

00:19:48.970 --> 00:19:53.720
or any other sites that we currently have,
come across on day-to-day life,

00:19:53.820 --> 00:19:57.260
we can understand that
color plays an important part.

00:19:59.190 --> 00:20:02.400
We have to make sure
that color contrast is

00:20:03.430 --> 00:20:06.420
met as per the standards of WCAG.

00:20:07.370 --> 00:20:11.340
For the standard text,
the minimum color contrast

00:20:11.570 --> 00:20:14.580
ratio is 4.5:1 with the background.

00:20:15.310 --> 00:20:18.150
The text needs to pass this criteria,

00:20:18.250 --> 00:20:21.510
and for the last text, it should be 3:1.

00:20:22.620 --> 00:20:29.620
For the non-text elements,
such as a graphical image

00:20:32.130 --> 00:20:36.730
or any other image that conveys
the information or the border

00:20:38.000 --> 00:20:42.200
of the input field or focus indicator,

00:20:42.400 --> 00:20:45.710
this should have a minimum contrast
ratio of 3:1.

00:20:46.570 --> 00:20:52.080
Incorporating accessibility
in your website

00:20:52.150 --> 00:20:56.280
will improve the look and feel along with

00:20:57.680 --> 00:21:01.110
a wide range of users.

00:21:05.030 --> 00:21:08.700
Remember a good contrast
doesn't just help people

00:21:08.800 --> 00:21:12.870
with disability,
it also improves the overall readability

00:21:13.100 --> 00:21:16.200
and usability of the web pages.

00:21:21.110 --> 00:21:23.370
Let's see what is the next--

00:21:30.580 --> 00:21:33.590
I wanted to add
one more point to the color.

00:21:34.020 --> 00:21:39.560
It's not just the color contrast,
there is one more part that is color alone

00:21:39.660 --> 00:21:43.200
also that we need to consider,
because we have

00:21:44.560 --> 00:21:49.670
people who have the condition
of color blindness.

00:21:50.370 --> 00:21:53.570
For them,
it is better to implement the pages

00:21:53.670 --> 00:21:57.780
that can be easily visible
and easily understandable.

00:21:58.110 --> 00:22:02.780
Make sure that you don't rely completely
on color to convey the information.

00:22:03.220 --> 00:22:06.790
Here in this example,
there is a link that says pages.

00:22:07.320 --> 00:22:12.290
If you notice, there is an underline
which stands out from other text.

00:22:12.930 --> 00:22:17.600
This will convey the colorblind user
that okay, this is something

00:22:17.700 --> 00:22:22.170
that is interactive and I can activate
this to get to the page.

00:22:24.540 --> 00:22:27.940
That was regarding the color.
Let's see the next

00:22:29.040 --> 00:22:31.180
part that we can incorporate

00:22:31.260 --> 00:22:34.180
in our designs, that is image.

00:22:35.220 --> 00:22:39.050
We cannot imagine an e-commerce website
without the product image, right?

00:22:39.450 --> 00:22:44.590
I mean, take any example, Amazon,
any of the example.

00:22:44.930 --> 00:22:47.930
Without image,
we cannot imagine a website.

00:22:48.200 --> 00:22:52.600
Images plays an important part
in enhancing the user interface

00:22:52.700 --> 00:22:54.130
of your website.

00:22:54.770 --> 00:22:57.770
The accessibility regarding image
is pretty much simple.

00:22:58.040 --> 00:23:00.540
If the image is decorative,

00:23:00.640 --> 00:23:02.440
hide them programmatically.

00:23:02.540 --> 00:23:07.110
If the IMG tag is used,
then the alt should be kept empty.

00:23:07.680 --> 00:23:11.420
If there is any other SVG image
or anything that is decorative,

00:23:11.750 --> 00:23:16.420
then you can provide area hidden
simply to hide the image from the user.

00:23:16.820 --> 00:23:21.420
If it is decorative, then
you don't have to provide any details.

00:23:22.860 --> 00:23:25.830
If the image is informative,
you have to make sure

00:23:25.930 --> 00:23:29.170
that a descriptive alternate text
is provided for the image.

00:23:30.070 --> 00:23:35.040
When a screen reader encounters
an image in the website,

00:23:35.310 --> 00:23:39.410
it reads out the alt text, helping
user understand what the image represent.

00:23:39.510 --> 00:23:42.550
Without alt text, these users

00:23:42.750 --> 00:23:45.750
would miss out
an important part of the image.

00:23:46.220 --> 00:23:49.310
Especially when we are creating
e-commerce websites,

00:23:49.510 --> 00:23:51.760
the product images are really important.

00:23:52.930 --> 00:23:56.770
If there is no description or anything
that is given for that product,

00:23:58.000 --> 00:24:01.800
then pretty much possible that
they might not be interested

00:24:01.950 --> 00:24:03.370
on the products.

00:24:04.240 --> 00:24:08.940
Just giving alternate text,
not just provide accessibility,

00:24:09.040 --> 00:24:12.850
but also improves your SEO
by helping search engines

00:24:12.950 --> 00:24:15.950
to understand the content of the images.

