and get that information.

00:28:52.940 --> 00:28:54.340
Next is about the layout

00:28:54.340 --> 00:28:57.040
and the design of your e-commerce site.

00:28:57.780 --> 00:29:01.480
It needs to be having
consistent navigation.

00:29:01.600 --> 00:29:02.720
What do we mean by this?

00:29:02.720 --> 00:29:05.890
Basically, when you are having certain

00:29:07.590 --> 00:29:10.530
navigation elements
in your header or footer,

00:29:10.640 --> 00:29:12.090
that needs to be consistent.

00:29:12.190 --> 00:29:16.000
Don't play around
just for the sake of making it

00:29:16.060 --> 00:29:19.670
more visually appealing
or making it fancy.

00:29:19.970 --> 00:29:22.700
You can still make a website fancy

00:29:22.800 --> 00:29:25.400
along with keeping
the accessibility intact.

00:29:25.860 --> 00:29:30.750
Just don't make
your navigation inconsistent,

00:29:30.930 --> 00:29:33.650
which will cause people with disabilities

00:29:33.750 --> 00:29:39.550
to really confusing experience
it will be, because they would say,

00:29:39.620 --> 00:29:42.250
okay, in header section, I have visited

00:29:42.350 --> 00:29:43.480
this particular link,

00:29:43.600 --> 00:29:46.040
but now that is not available
in header section.

00:29:46.820 --> 00:29:48.490
Where the hell did that link go?

00:29:48.490 --> 00:29:50.400
Or, where the hell that button went?

00:29:51.060 --> 00:29:54.300
You need to ensure the navigation
should be consistent.

00:29:54.870 --> 00:29:58.200
Apart from that, in this era or age,
I can say

00:29:59.140 --> 00:30:02.210
mobile users are far more compared

00:30:02.310 --> 00:30:07.080
to someone who is browsing on a desktop,

00:30:07.180 --> 00:30:12.240
be it mobile, be it tablet,
be it any handheld device.

00:30:13.090 --> 00:30:16.120
Those are very popular
nowadays compared to desktop

00:30:16.220 --> 00:30:19.460
when it comes to browsing
or shopping for any product.

00:30:20.260 --> 00:30:23.700
We do have lots of apps as well,
as you all know.

00:30:24.160 --> 00:30:29.200
Making the e-commerce site responsive

00:30:29.200 --> 00:30:31.130
would be a very important part

00:30:31.870 --> 00:30:34.470
when it comes to the accessibility.

00:30:34.740 --> 00:30:38.910
Any users can interact with the website.

00:30:39.010 --> 00:30:44.550
As I said, accessibility is ensuring that

00:30:44.550 --> 00:30:47.150
they can access the site the way they want

00:30:47.790 --> 00:30:50.620
and whichever tool
they want to use, they can.

00:30:51.760 --> 00:30:53.890
Apart from that, resize and reflow.

00:30:53.990 --> 00:30:56.040
When it comes to resize,

00:30:56.350 --> 00:31:00.400
ensuring that your text can resize as per
the zoom level

00:31:00.500 --> 00:31:04.200
that a user is using on
their browsers is also important.

00:31:04.670 --> 00:31:08.370
Someone with a low vision would be unable

00:31:08.440 --> 00:31:11.820
to see the small text
that is placed on the screen.

00:31:12.410 --> 00:31:16.220
They would definitely would want

00:31:16.320 --> 00:31:18.920
to zoom in the screen and understand

00:31:19.020 --> 00:31:21.620
what is all that information about.

00:31:22.590 --> 00:31:25.890
When it comes to reflow again,
you need to ensure

00:31:26.730 --> 00:31:28.430
there is a single columnar view

00:31:28.530 --> 00:31:31.100
available for your e-commerce site.

00:31:31.200 --> 00:31:33.200
Wherein user don't have to use

00:31:33.300 --> 00:31:35.630
like the horizontal scroll bars

00:31:35.730 --> 00:31:37.970
to access the information.

00:31:39.240 --> 00:31:45.310
When it comes to orientation, again,
it's about the mobile devices,

00:31:45.310 --> 00:31:48.010
especially because some people,

00:31:48.810 --> 00:31:50.620
like people who use wheelchair,

00:31:50.650 --> 00:31:54.690
they might want to mount
the devices on the wheelchair

00:31:54.850 --> 00:31:59.260
and maybe to see a larger view,
what they are trying to browse also.

00:31:59.730 --> 00:32:03.130
They would want to orient
the device in a landscape mode.

00:32:03.900 --> 00:32:07.200
If you don't enable that

00:32:07.330 --> 00:32:11.240
orientation in the way
the user wants into a landscape

00:32:11.340 --> 00:32:14.510
or portrait,
it will block them from using your site.

00:32:14.610 --> 00:32:18.480
Because that experience will not be good
and they might go

00:32:18.580 --> 00:32:22.780
to a different e-commerce site
and will lose a customer in that case.

00:32:24.080 --> 00:32:25.850
Having a logical reading order,

00:32:26.440 --> 00:32:29.350
it's all about
like how you read something.

00:32:29.560 --> 00:32:33.630
Like when you're trying to read a story,
you don't necessarily

00:32:33.760 --> 00:32:38.460
start from the initial chapter
and directly jumps to the last one.

00:32:39.030 --> 00:32:42.770
If it was in that manner,
the first, the fourth, and then seven,

00:32:43.340 --> 00:32:45.840
in this manner,
the chapters are placed, you definitely

00:32:45.940 --> 00:32:49.010
won't get the head
and tail of that particular story.

00:32:49.940 --> 00:32:56.550
Ensuring the content order is in logical
way plays an important role

00:32:56.650 --> 00:32:58.530
in your e-commerce site.

00:32:58.800 --> 00:33:02.220
If I take an example
of this screenshot itself,

00:33:02.370 --> 00:33:05.960
it's a cart page, which is having
a product image, the product

00:33:06.060 --> 00:33:10.160
details, the name of the product,
the price, quantity, the subtotal.

00:33:11.030 --> 00:33:14.770
In this case, ensuring that it starts from

00:33:14.970 --> 00:33:18.370
top to bottom and left to right
would be an important thing.

00:33:19.100 --> 00:33:22.540
Otherwise, the information
will not be conveyed in an effective manner.

00:33:23.040 --> 00:33:25.980
Again, it will not be a good experience.

00:33:26.200 --> 00:33:29.620
From an accessibility point of view
as well, it will be a failure.

00:33:33.290 --> 00:33:34.820
Coming to custom elements,

00:33:34.920 --> 00:33:39.490
which Athira was also mentioning earlier,
that you can add custom elements

00:33:39.890 --> 00:33:44.730
and ensure that different interactions
that are there, you can easily develop,

00:33:44.840 --> 00:33:47.030
create on your e-commerce site.

00:33:47.730 --> 00:33:50.770
When it comes to custom elements,
three important things are there,

00:33:50.870 --> 00:33:53.440
name, role, value, when it comes

00:33:53.540 --> 00:33:56.140
to identifying that particular element.

00:33:57.010 --> 00:33:59.610
As you can see, there is a screenshot

00:33:59.980 --> 00:34:03.420
which consists of a tabbed interface code.

00:34:04.980 --> 00:34:07.590
You can basically create any component

00:34:07.990 --> 00:34:11.060
in your customized way
by adding your own code

00:34:11.460 --> 00:34:14.990
and adding your own CSS into it,
and ensure that

00:34:15.460 --> 00:34:17.860
by following the accessibility practices,

00:34:17.960 --> 00:34:20.460
the interaction is accessible.

00:34:21.470 --> 00:34:25.340
Your customized elements
needs to have an accessible name,

00:34:25.500 --> 00:34:28.610
so users can understand
what that element is all about.

00:34:29.070 --> 00:34:31.980
It needs to have a role,
so user can understand

00:34:32.440 --> 00:34:36.950
what action that particular element
will be performing like a button or a tab.

00:34:37.050 --> 00:34:39.620
Button I'll say stick to native.

00:34:39.720 --> 00:34:42.890
Whatever elements are present natively,

00:34:42.990 --> 00:34:45.990
I'll urge to stick
to native implementation,

00:34:46.090 --> 00:34:50.130
because that provides
accessibility out of the box

00:34:50.430 --> 00:34:54.400
and you don't have to fiddle
much around the accessibility of it.

00:34:55.300 --> 00:34:59.470
Yes, when you customize it, role
is an important part, because role tab

00:34:59.640 --> 00:35:02.240
currently it's not in a native format

00:35:02.640 --> 00:35:05.310
but you need to use ARIA in that case.

00:35:06.380 --> 00:35:08.980
Apart from that, required role,

