00:35:51.920 --> 00:35:54.930
not only helps describe its purpose,

00:35:55.560 --> 00:35:57.600
it also helps to understand what

00:35:57.600 --> 00:36:00.200
the element is all about.

00:36:01.500 --> 00:36:03.400
This is a very interesting feature

00:36:03.400 --> 00:36:06.310
that most of the browsers provide now.

00:36:06.410 --> 00:36:08.010
It's called accessibility tree.

00:36:08.010 --> 00:36:12.410
It sits in your developer
dev tools in your browsers.

00:36:13.310 --> 00:36:17.280
When you inspect any element,
like when you create something

00:36:18.020 --> 00:36:21.820
