00:37:06.970 --> 00:37:10.740
Making your elements accessible
by providing

00:37:10.840 --> 00:37:14.810
an accessible name is an important feature
when it comes to accessibility.

00:37:16.110 --> 00:37:21.150
Ensure your elements are not
identically labeled or identically named,

00:37:21.810 --> 00:37:25.520
because it will confuse the user
who is using a screen reader.

00:37:25.620 --> 00:37:29.960
Not only screen reader,
but also someone with mobility impairment

00:37:30.390 --> 00:37:35.930
if they're using a speech
recognition software, like in iOS

00:37:36.030 --> 00:37:40.170
there is voice control or in Android
there is voice access as well.

00:37:40.730 --> 00:37:44.240
If they are trying to use that to interact
with elements on the page,

00:37:44.640 --> 00:37:47.470
they won't be able to reach
where they want

00:37:47.910 --> 00:37:50.640
if all the elements are named
in the same way.

00:37:51.510 --> 00:37:55.650
A minute differentiator needs to be there

00:37:55.850 --> 00:37:58.450
to make it more descriptive.

00:38:00.850 --> 00:38:06.020
Apart from that,
I'll also say it needs to be not ambiguous,

00:38:06.150 --> 00:38:07.530
it needs to be descriptive

00:38:07.790 --> 00:38:10.800
so that user can understand
the purpose of that particular element.

00:38:13.470 --> 00:38:15.600
Coming to keyboard navigation,

