00:39:14.090 --> 00:39:17.400
As soon as my focus lands
on that particular element,

00:39:17.500 --> 00:39:18.860
it will be a border of purple color,

00:39:20.000 --> 00:39:23.500
so I know where my current focus
is on with the keyboard.

00:39:24.440 --> 00:39:27.140
Also following a logical focus order.

00:39:27.710 --> 00:39:30.310
In case of header, main and footer,

00:39:30.840 --> 00:39:33.450
there would be lots
of interactive elements.

00:39:34.080 --> 00:39:36.880
Visually,
if they are in a particular order,

00:39:37.420 --> 00:39:41.690
it needs to receive the keyboard focus
also in that particular order.

00:39:42.190 --> 00:39:44.790
If you break that focus order,

00:39:45.160 --> 00:39:49.160
it will break the semantics

00:39:49.160 --> 00:39:53.830
because user will be confused
that they are jumping all over the page.

00:39:54.300 --> 00:39:56.900
They're not going in a logical sequence.

00:39:58.000 --> 00:40:01.040
When it comes to focus order
and reading order,

00:40:01.140 --> 00:40:04.580
it needs to be from left to right
and top to bottom.

00:40:04.980 --> 00:40:07.550
Always remember that.

